</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-32_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>Health and safety training encompasses the provision of information, instruction, and supervision to employees, ensuring they understand the risks associated with their work and how to mitigate them.







 

  
<br>
</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-34_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Hazard</strong> - Any potential source of harm or adverse health effect on a person or persons.


























































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Risk</strong> - The likelihood that a hazard will cause harm, combined with the severity of that harm.




























































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-39_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-40_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-41_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation, regulations, and best practice</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-43_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-44_ pf-text-1">The Health and Safety at Work Act 1974 serves as the primary legislative framework in the UK, placing a duty of care on employers to ensure their employees' health, safety, and welfare.



























































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-46_ pf-text-1">Regulations such as the Management of Health and Safety at Work Regulations 1999 and the Control of Substances Hazardous to Health (COSHH) Regulations 2002 provide specific guidance on managing risks and hazards in the workplace.





























































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-48_ pf-text-1">Best practices include conducting regular risk assessments, providing adequate training and supervision, and fostering a safety culture through effective communication and employee engagement.






























































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-50_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-51_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-52_ pf-heading-1-h3">Importance of health and safety training</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-54_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-55_ pf-text-1"><strong>Mitigating risks </strong>- Health and safety training equips employees with the knowledge and skills to identify potential hazards and take appropriate measures to mitigate risks, thereby reducing the likelihood of accidents and injuries.
















































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-57_ pf-text-1"><strong>Legal compliance</strong> - Compliance with health and safety legislation is a legal requirement and a moral obligation. Effective training ensures that employers meet their duty of care obligations and uphold the rights of their workforce.




























































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-59_ pf-text-1"><strong>Promoting productivity</strong> - A safe working environment boosts employee morale, productivity, and retention. Investing in health and safety training demonstrates a commitment to employee well-being, fostering a positive workplace culture.





























































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-61_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-62_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-63_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations
